LORE saltglass-reach
FLAGS WILDERNESS MERCHANT
- Saltglass Reach: overland desert corridor from pyramid settlements to Mafdet;
  salt flats reflect sunlight with disorienting intensity
- Sand-pirate raids are frequent and organized; pirates have informants in
  departure cities; randomize departure times and travel with armed escort
- Sand-Sea Carters' Guild controls Reach transit; contracts non-negotiable;
  buy their gap-location intelligence before leaving the road
- Water sources: sparse, mapped, and known to Guild carriers; unknown travelers
  have died finding out the hard way; get the map before you go
- Eye protection required on the flats in full sun; hours of exposure causes
  vision impairment; Khephari polarized-light vision makes them best guides
- Measure's Rest: Saltglass Reach Wardens' cairn tablet library; Jade Magistracy
  (Kowloon) funds expeditions here for Littoral Branch source documents;
  the Wardens want information in exchange, not coin
~
